fs.fibu2.data.model
Class Entry

java.lang.Object
  fs.fibu2.data.model.Entry
All Implemented Interfaces:
XMLConfigurable
public final class Entry
extends java.lang.Object
implements XMLConfigurable

This class represents an fsfibu2 journal entry. It is immutable, at least as far as its account object is immutable (Since Account is an abstract class, no guarantee can be made as to whether the object is immutable).

Author:
Simon Hampe

Entry

public Entry(java.lang.String name,
             float value,
             java.util.Currency currency,
             java.util.GregorianCalendar date,
             Category category,
             java.lang.String account,
             java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> accountInformation,
             java.lang.String additionalInformation)
      throws java.lang.NullPointerException,
             java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
Creates an entry with values set to the given parameters

Parameters:
name - The name of this entry, e.g. 'Getränkeeinnahmen'. A null string is interpreted as empty string.
value - The value of this entry, e.g. '140,00'.
currency - The currency of this entry, e.g. EUR. Must not be null.
date - The date of this entry, e.g. 13.4.2009. Must not be null.
category - The category of this entry, e.g. 'Getränke / Süßigkeiten - Einnahmen'. The null category is interpreted as the root category
account - The account id of this entry, e.g. 'bank_account'. Must be known to the AccountLoader
accountInformation - A list of information specific for the account type, e.g. account sheet number. Null is interpreted as the empty list.
additionalInformation - Some additional information for this entry, e.g. 'Beinhaltet 5 Euro Bestechung von Fex, damit er seinen Fuffziger kleinmachen durfte.' A null string is interpreted as the empty string
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - - If any of the values where 'Must not be null' is written, is null.
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - - If the account ID is null or unknown to the AccountLoader
